<div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Are $1d, $2d and $3d safe to use ?<br /></div><br /><br />Yes. If you look at the <a href="http://nesdevwiki.ath.cx/index.php/NTSC_Video#Brightness_Levels" class="postlink">brightness levels on the Wiki</a>, you'll see that only $0D outputs a negative level. $1D is the same as $xF, $2D is a bit less than $00, and $3D is very close to $10.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Fri Jun 16, 2006 5:09 am</p><hr />
